					<ul>
					<ul><span>Scientific Name</span>: Tursiops truncatus </ul>
					<ul><span>Average Weight</span>: 1,100 lbs </ul>
					<ul><span>Average Lifespan in the Wild</span>: 45 years </ul>
					<ul><span>Diet</span>: Other kinds of fish</ul>
					</ul>
				<p> 
				In the wild, these sleek swimmers can reach speeds of over 18 miles an hour. 
				They surface often to breathe, doing so two or three times a minute. 
				Schools have been known to come to the aid of an injured dolphin and help it to the surface.
